name: Baba Au Rhum, Anjuna

reviews.review_text: Baba Au Rhum is a wonderful cafe with amazing breakfast and brunch options. I tried their omelette and pasta, and both were absolutely delicious! The juice was super refreshing, a perfect addition to the meal. I went there for brunch, and the vibes were just incredible. The combination of trance music and great food made the experience so enjoyable. The ambiance is cozy and laid-back, surrounded by greenery, making it a great spot to relax and unwind. It‚Äôs definitely a place I‚Äôd recommend for a chilled-out brunch in Goa!

This place was one of the best places to eat in Goa when I visited it last year but their taste has gone down.
I had ordered Pizza, white sauce Pasta,vanilla in house ice cream and tomato soup.

The tomato soup was not as good as it was last time, it was too sour

The Pasta was very bland

The Pizza was okay okay

The inhouse ice cream was the same as we would get in the local shop nothing different.

It's a good place to visit but it's your luck if you get good taste food or not

4 years in a row to Goa for Christmas but this was the first time we visited this place and I have to thank my sister for suggesting it coz this place had some delicious food and an amazing atmosphere!

Just go and try the Leo‚Äôs special, it‚Äôs been a week and I can still feel the way it tasted in my mouth ü§§üòã You will love it and if you like croissant you will definitely fall in love with it!

Apart from that we tried some prawns, don‚Äôt remember the exact name but tasted delicious, and their cocktails were good too! A must try place in Goa!
